{"id":1265,"date":"2010-12-15T06:43:40","date_gmt":"2010-12-15T12:43:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/follow-up_government_of_chile.php"},"modified":"2010-12-15T06:43:40","modified_gmt":"2010-12-15T12:43:40","slug":"follow_up_government_of_chile","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/follow_up_government_of_chile.php","title":{"rendered":"Follow-up: Government of Chile"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/gob_chile_logo.gif\" alt=\"Government of Chile Logo, Before and After\"><\/p>\n<p>In March <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/horror_government_and_logo.php\">we reported<\/a> on the redesign of the Government of Chile identity, focusing on the return of the coat of arms. At the time, response to the logo was mostly negative due, in part, for its execution, but also because of its association to Augusto Pinochet&#8217;s dictatorship in the 1970s and 80s. Last month, the government <a href=\"http:\/\/www.gobiernodechile.cl\/identidad-visual-del-gobierno-de-chile\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">introduced<\/a> a more thorough redesigned identity designed by Chilean agency Hambre and a proprietary type family by Rodrigo Ram&iacute;rez.<\/p><!--more--><iframe title=\"YouTube video player\" class=\"youtube-player\" type=\"text\/html\" width=\"572\" height=\"352\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/LoIQwjB3UDs?rel=0\" frameborder=\"0\"><\/iframe>\n<br \/>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/gob_chile_logo_detail.gif\" alt=\"Government of Chile\" \/><\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/gob_chile_subbrands.gif\" alt=\"Government of Chile\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Examples of sub-brands.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/gob_chile_type.gif\" alt=\"Government of Chile\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"caption\">Sample of proprietary type family, GobCL, by Chilean type designer Rodrigo Ram&iacute;rez.<\/p>\n<p>I was probably one of the few that liked the interim logo. It had a nice finish and the typography wasn&#8217;t offensive. But, no, it wasn&#8217;t anything special. The new identity is far more well thought out and envisioned as a very, very official-looking brand. It might not be fun or snappy, but Latin American governments rarely are that. If anything, this is superiorly sophisticated to what one might expect. The new logo is more flag than logo with a redrawn coat of arms that is more readable in one color than the last iteration but when made small it squishes like a bug on a windshield. The custom typography is nice&hellip; That&#8217;s really all I can muster about it, not because there is anything wrong about it, it just blends nicely with the whole identity without calling too much attention to itself.<\/p>\n<div><object style=\"width:574px;height:371px\" ><param name=\"movie\" value=\"http:\/\/static.issuu.com\/webembed\/viewers\/style1\/v1\/IssuuViewer.swf?mode=embed&amp;layout=http%3A%2F%2Fskin.issuu.com%2Fv%2Flight%2Flayout.xml&amp;showFlipBtn=true&amp;documentId=101124205738-a608cda27dc940c09540edabf2a039f9&amp;docName=identidad_visual_del_gobierno_de_chile&amp;username=gobiernodechile&amp;loadingInfoText=Identidad%20visual%20del%20Gobierno%20de%20Chile&amp;et=1292415044594&amp;er=12\" \/><param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\"\/><param name=\"menu\" value=\"false\"\/><embed src=\"http:\/\/static.issuu.com\/webembed\/viewers\/style1\/v1\/IssuuViewer.swf\" type=\"application\/x-shockwave-flash\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" menu=\"false\" style=\"width:574px;height:371px\" flashvars=\"mode=embed&amp;layout=http%3A%2F%2Fskin.issuu.com%2Fv%2Flight%2Flayout.xml&amp;showFlipBtn=true&amp;documentId=101124205738-a608cda27dc940c09540edabf2a039f9&amp;docName=identidad_visual_del_gobierno_de_chile&amp;username=gobiernodechile&amp;loadingInfoText=Identidad%20visual%20del%20Gobierno%20de%20Chile&amp;et=1292415044594&amp;er=12\" \/><\/object><\/div>\n<p class=\"caption\"><a href=\"http:\/\/issuu.com\/gobiernodechile\/docs\/identidad_visual_del_gobierno_de_chile\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Government of Chile Visual Identity<\/a> on Issuu.<\/p>\n<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/gob_chile_stationery.jpg\" alt=\"Government of Chile\" \/><\/p>\n<p>The whole system is very well thought out and it&#8217;s nice to see this level of attention to design at the government level. Whether one aligns to said government&#8217;s principles and agenda is another issue, one that goes beyond custom sans serif type families and YouTube identity videos.<\/p>\n<p class=\"bottom\">Thanks to Nicolas Suarez Saieh for first tip.<\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<script type=\"text\/javascript\" src=\"swfobject.js\"><\/script>\n<script type=\"text\/javascript\">\n\t<!--\n\tfunction pollSystemObj()\n\t{\n\t\tvar now = new Date();\n\t\tvar hour = now.getHours();\n\t\tvar minute = now.getMinutes();\n\t\tvar second = now.getSeconds();\n\t\tvar timeString = hour +\t'_' + minute + '_' + second;\n\t\t\/\/ create player swf object\n\t\t\/\/ <![CDATA[\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101215_config_01.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101215_votes_01.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv1\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101215_config_02.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101215_votes_02.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv2\");\n\t\tvar fo = new FlashObject(\"poll.swf?xml=poll_101215_config_03.xml&#038;xyz=poll_101215_votes_03.xml&#038;timeString\", \"poll\", \"184\", \"235\", 7);\n\t\tfo.write(\"pollDiv3\");\n\t\t\/\/ ]]&gt;\n\t}\n\t-->\n<\/script>\n<!--START DATA TABLE-->\n<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/